## Reasoning
1. The issue mentioned is related to the unnecessary use of `@Produces` annotation in Quarkus when the producer method is annotated with a scope annotation, a stereotype, or a qualifier.
2. In this case, the `produceLog` method is not annotated with any of the mentioned annotations, so we can remove the `@Produces` annotation.
3. Instead of using the `@Produces` annotation, we can create a getter method annotated with `@Named` to access the `Logger` field.

## Updated java File
```java
package com.redhat.coolstore.utils;

import jakarta.inject.Named;
import jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;
import java.util.logging.Logger;

public class Producers {

    Logger log = Logger.getLogger(Producers.class.getName());

    @Named
    public Logger getLog(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {
        return Logger.getLogger(injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName());
    }

}
```

